The '''Canadian Association of Emergency Physicians''' ('''CAEP''') is the [[professional association]] of [[emergency physician]]s in [[Canada]]. It is also known in [[French language|French]] as ''Association Canadienne Des Medecins d'Urgence'' (''ACMU''). The official journal of the CAEP is the [[Canadian Journal of Emergency Medicine]].

The CAEP helped found the [[International Federation for Emergency Medicine]] in 1991 along with the [[American College of Emergency Physicians]] (ACEP), the [[Australasian College for Emergency Medicine]] (ACEM), and the (then) [[Royal College of Emergency Medicine|British Association for Emergency Medicine]] (BAEM) .

